{"word":"μογιλάλος","slug":"μογιλάλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>μογιλάλος, ον</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:μόγις\">μόγις</a>, λάλος</el> ‘talkative’] ‘deficient in uttering audible sounds’, <b>speech-impaired <a href='B:480 7:32'>Mk 7:32</a></b> (<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ vs.\">vs.</a> 35). Others interpret as inability to make an intelligible sound, <b>mute.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:μογγιλάλος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:μόγις\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}